1	As an Admin, I want to add users by entering their emails and roles so that only authorized users can access the system.	3	Feature	To Do	Admin can enter email, select role        (team leader, team_member), and submit form. System validates email format. User is added to Firestore users collection with isActive=true. Duplicate email check prevents duplicates. Success or error message is displayed.
2	As a user, I want to sign up using my email so that I can create an account.	5	Feature	Done	User enters email, password, and confirms password. Firebase Auth creates user account. User document is created in Firestore with role from admin pre-assignment. Email verification is sent. User cannot log in until email is verified.
3	As a registered user, I want to log in to the system so that I can access authorized features.	3	Feature	Done	User enters email and password. Firebase Auth validates credentials. On success, user is redirected based on role. On failure, error message is shown. Session persists across page reloads.
4	As a user, I want to log out from the system so that my session ends securely.	1	Feature	Done	Logout button is visible in navigation. Clicking logout signs user out of Firebase Auth. Session storage is cleared. User is redirected to login page.
5	As a user, I want to reset my password so that I can regain access if I forget it.	2	Feature	To Do	Forgot Password link is on login page. User enters email and receives password reset email. User can set new password via email link.
6	As a Team Leader, I want to view all projects I have created so that I can manage them.	2	Feature	Done	Dashboard shows list of projects created by the logged-in leader. Each project shows name, status, creation date. Empty state message when no projects exist.
7	As a Team Leader, I want to create a new project so that I can organize work for my team.	3	Feature	Done	Create Project button opens form with name, description, deadline. Project is saved to Firestore with status="draft", leaderId=current user. Project appears in project list immediately.
8	As a Team Leader, I want to add team members to a project so that they can be assigned tasks.	3	Feature	To Do	Leader can select from list of existing team members (role="team_member"). Selected member is added to project's members subcollection. Member appears in project team list. Leader can remove members from project.
9	As a Team Leader, I want to upload a requirements document for analysis so that potential vulnerabilities can be detected.	5	Feature	Done	Leader can upload .txt or .pdf file. File is sent to Python FastAPI backend (/analyze endpoint). Analysis results are stored in Firestore analysisResults collection. Progress indicator shown during analysis. Results page displays vulnerabilities with severity, impact, likelihood, CVE match.
10	As a Team Leader, I want to view analysis results in a structured table so that I can understand detected potential vulnerabilities.	3	Feature	Done	Results table shows Requirement, Severity, Impact, Likelihood, Top CVE, Similarity, CVE Description. Chips display severity (High/Medium/Low) with appropriate colors. Table is sortable by severity and risk level. Duplicate requirements are filtered out.
11	As a Team Leader, I want to create tasks from detected potential vulnerabilities so that team members can fix them.	5	Feature	To Do	From analysis results, leader can click Create Task on any vulnerability. Task form pre-populates with requirement text. Leader can set title, assignee, priority (High/Medium/Low), deadline. Task is saved to Firestore tasks collection with status="open". Assigned team member receives notification.
12	As a Team Leader, I want to assign tasks to team members so that responsibilities are clear.	2	Feature	To Do	Task creation form includes dropdown of project members (role="team_member"). Only members added to the project appear in dropdown. Assignee name is stored with task.
13	As a Team Leader, I want to be notified when a team member submits a task so that I can review it promptly.	3	Feature	To Do	Notification appears in leader's dashboard when task status changes to "for_review". Notification shows task title and submitter name. Unread notifications are highlighted. Clicking notification navigates to task review page.
14	As a Team Leader, I want to review a submitted task so that I can accept or reject the work.	5	Feature	To Do	Leader can view original requirement vs. proposed changes side-by-side. Leader can approve task (status="approved"). Leader can reject task with comment (status="rejected"). If approved, changes are committed to final requirements document. If rejected, team member is notified with comment.
15	As a Team Leader, I want to compare two versions of a requirements document so that I can see security improvements.	5	Feature	To Do	Leader can select two requirement versions from dropdown. Side-by-side comparison shows original and revised text. Differences are highlighted (added text in green, removed text in red). Dashboard shows resolved vs. remaining vulnerabilities. Progress metrics (percentage improved) are displayed.
16	As a Team Member, I want to view projects I am part of so that I know what I'm working on.	2	Feature	To Do	Dashboard shows list of projects where user is a member. Each project shows name, status, team leader name.
17	As a Team Member, I want to view tasks assigned to me so that I know what to work on.	2	Feature	To Do	Task board shows all tasks assigned to current user. Tasks are grouped by status (Open, In Progress, For Review, Approved, Rejected). Each task shows title, priority, deadline, and description.
18	As a Team Member, I want to receive notifications when I am assigned a new task so that I don't miss it.	3	Feature	To Do	Notification appears in member's dashboard when task is assigned. Notification shows task title and deadline. Email notification (optional) can be configured.
19	As a Team Member, I want to submit my work on a task so that the leader can review it.	3	Feature	To Do	Member can select a task and submit proposed changes (text area). Submission updates task status to "for_review". Leader is notified of submission. Member cannot re-submit until leader reviews.
20	As a Team Member, I want to view feedback on rejected tasks so that I know what to fix.	2	Feature	To Do	When task is rejected, leader's comment is displayed. Rejected task shows Revision Needed status. Comment is visible on task detail page.
21	As any user, I want to ask a chatbot questions about CVE so that I can learn about vulnerabilities.	5	Feature	To Do	Chatbot interface is accessible from all pages. User can type questions (e.g., "What is CVE-89?", "How to fix SQL injection?"). Chatbot responds with CVE description and mitigation using local knowledge base. Chat history is displayed in conversation format. Loading indicator shows while processing.
22	As any user, I want the chatbot to recognize CVE IDs so that I can quickly look them up.	3	Feature	To Do	Chatbot detects CVE pattern (e.g., "CVE-89", "CVE-306") in user input. Returns relevant information from CVE knowledge base. If CVE not found, suggests searching official CVE database.

